✅ Step 3: Access Nagios Dashboard
Open browser:
http://localhost:8888
Login with:
Username: nagiosadmin
Password: nagios
Inside Nagios, you can explore:
Hosts → machines/services being monitored
Services → checks like CPU, disk, HTTP, etc.
Alerts → recent warnings/critical alerts
✅ Step 4: View Host Details
In the Nagios web UI, go to Hosts.
Click on a host name (like localhost).
You can now see:
Host Status → UP / DOWN
Metrics → CPU, memory, network (depending on checks configured)
Actions → reschedule checks, disable notifications, schedule downtime, etc.

